  "narrative": {
    "intro": "NAICS 541715 obligations for FY2026 to date total $25.5B across 12,954 awards with an average award size of $2M. Obligations fell 45.0% year over year. Annual obligations rose from $29B in FY21 to a peak of $46.3B in FY25 before declining to $25.5B in FY26 to date. The Department of Defense accounted for the largest share of FY2026 to date buy at $16.2B, followed by the National Aeronautics and Space Administration at $3.9B and the Department of Energy at $3.4B. Other agencies with notable FY2026 to date obligations include the General Services Administration at $798M and the Department of Health and Human Services at $793M. Major vendors receiving the largest FY2026 to date obligations include FLUOR MARINE PROPULSION, LLC at $3.8B, CALIFORNIA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY at $1.6B, and THE JOHNS HOPKINS UNIVERSITY APPLIED PHYSICS LABORATORY LLC at $1.1B. The FY26 to date profile shows concentrated spending by a few agencies and vendors amid an overall year-over-year decline.",
    "sections": [
