        "heading": "How has FY2026 to date spending trended compared with prior years?",
        "body": "Obligations declined after multiple years of growth, with FY26 to date at $25.5B compared with $46.3B in FY25 and $43.2B in FY24. The sector rose from $29B in FY21 to $46.3B in FY25 before obligations fell 45.0% year over year into FY26 to date."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate the FY2026 to date market?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense is the dominant buyer at $16.2B, followed by NASA at $3.9B and the Department of Energy at $3.4B. Top vendors by FY26 to date obligations include FLUOR MARINE PROPULSION, LLC at $3.8B, CALIFORNIA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY at $1.6B, and THE JOHNS HOPKINS UNIVERSITY APPLIED PHYSICS LABORATORY LLC at $1.1B."
      }
